ions%20and%20low%20morale%2C%20folded%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20HTS's%20blitz.%20Predictably%2C%20Western%20powers%20have%20swooped%20in%20to%20shape%20Syria's%20political%20future%20and%20are%20now%20vying%20to%20influence%20the%20makeup%20of%20the%20next%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20relative%20calm%20of%20India%20or%20from%20the%20peaceful%20Western%20European%20capitals%2C%20it's%20tempting%20to%20ask%3A%20why%20is%20the%20Arab%20world%20perpetually%20at%20war%20with%20itself%3F%20Why%20does%20it%20spawn%20so%20many%20extremist%20groups%3F%20Why%20has%20it%20been%20trapped%20in%20cycles%20of%20violence%20and%20instability%20for%20decades%3F%20To%20answer%20these%20questions%2C%20we%20must%20look%20beyond%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20all%20the%20way%20back%20to%20the%2011th%20century.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20let's%20stay%20within%20the%20last%20century%20to%20understand%20how%20history%20has%20shaped%20the%20region's%20current%20turmoil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%3Cem%3ELawrence%3C%2Fem%3E%20Syndrome%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20I%20watched%20%3Cem%3ELawrence%20of%20Arabia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20sweeping%20tale%20of%20West%20Asia's%20chaos%20around%20the%20years%201916-17.%20Hollywood%2C%20as%20we%20know%2C%20isn't%20big%20on%20sequels.%20But%20looking%20at%20the%20current%20mess%20in%20the%20region%2C%20I%20would%20certainly%20say%2C%20no%2C%20shout%2C%20that%20it's%20high%20time%20for%20a%20sequel%20to%20Lawrence%20of%20Arabia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20iconic%201962%20film%20serves%20as%20a%20powerful%20metaphor%20for%20the%20ongoing%20struggles%20in%20West%20Asia.%20The%20themes%20of%20betrayal%2C%20tribalism%20and%20Western%20manipulation%20in%20the%20film%20echo%20the%20realities%20of%20modern%20conflicts%20in%20Syria%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Yemen%20and%20Libya.%20Set%20during%20World%20War%20I%2C%20the%20film%20offers%20a%20stark%20window%20into%20the%20forces%20that%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20region's%20instability.%20The%20movie%20depicts%20T.E.%20Lawrence%2C%20played%20by%20Peter%20O'Toole%2C%20as%20a%20British%20officer%20cobbling%20together%20a%20front%20consisting%20of%20diverse%20groups%20of%20Arab%20tribes%20to%20fight%20against%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire%2C%20which%20had%20governed%20much%20of%20the%20Arab%20world%20for%20centuries.%20The%20British%20officer%20on%20behalf%20of%20his%20government%20promised%20the%20Arabs%20full%20independence%20in%20return%20for%20their%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20history%20shows%2C%20that%20promise%20was%20nothing%20more%20than%20deception.%20After%20the%20war%2C%20the%20secret%20Sykes-Picot%20Agreement%2C%20signed%20between%20Britain%20and%20France%2C%20carved%20the%20region%20into%20British%20and%20French%20colonial%20spheres%20of%20influence%2C%20betraying%20the%20Arabs%20and%20ignoring%20their%20aspirations%20for%20self-determination.%20This%20betrayal%20was%20not%20just%20a%20diplomatic%20slight%E2%80%94it%20planted%20the%20seeds%20of%20mistrust%20that%20continue%20to%20shape%20Arab-Western%20relations%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arbitrary%20borders%20drawn%20by%20colonial%20powers%2C%20with%20no%20regard%20for%20the%20region's%20ethnic%2C%20tribal%20or%20religious%20complexities%2C%20created%20fragile%20states%20that%20were%20prone%20to%20fracture.%20Syria%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Libya%20and%20Yemen%20are%20glaring%20examples%20of%20this%20legacy%3A%20nations%20artificially%20built%20by%20outsiders%2C%20now%20disintegrating%20as%20factions%20fight%20for%20power%20in%20structures%20never%20designed%20to%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFragile%20Tribal%20Alliances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMemorable%20but%20controversial%20views%20about%20the%20Arabs%20uttered%20in%20Lawrence%20of%20Arabia%20are%20believed%20by%20many%20in%20the%20West%20even%20today%3A%20%26quot%3BSo%20long%20as%20the%20Arabs%20fight%20tribe%20against%20tribe%2C%20so%20long%20will%20they%20be%20a%20little%20people%2C%20a%20silly%20people%E2%80%94greedy%2C%20barbarous%2C%20and%20cruel%2C%20as%20you%20are.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20film%2C%20Lawrence%20struggles%20to%20unite%20the%20disparate%20Arab%20tribes%20against%20the%20Ottomans.%20This%20reflects%20the%20tribalism%20and%20factionalism%20that%20continue%20to%20plague%20the%20region.%20In%20Libya%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20fall%20of%20Muammar%20Gaddafi%20exposed%20deep%20tribal%20rivalries%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20prolonged%20civil%20war.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20Yemen%2C%20the%20conflict%20is%20partly%20driven%20by%20tribal%20and%20sectarian%20divisions%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20foreign%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20All%20About%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20desert%2C%20and%20no%20man%20needs%20nothing%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Lawrence%20in%20the%20film.%20But%20things%20dramatically%20changed%20in%20the%20region%20with%20the%20discovery%20of%20vast%20oil%20reserves.%20From%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20region's%20desert%20became%20resource-rich.%20Oil%20turned%20deserts%20into%20global%20battlegrounds%2C%20amplifying%20foreign%20intervention.%20Another%20Hollywood%20movie%2C%20Syriana%2C%20depicts%20how%20mega%20Western%20energy%20companies%20played%20kingmakers%20in%20the%20region.%20Greed%20led%20to%20corruption%20and%20manipulation.%20In%20our%20times%2C%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20have%20often%20supported%20local%20leaders%20or%20factions%20in%20ways%20that%20serve%20their%20strategic%20interests%2C%20only%20to%20abandon%20them%20later.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20US%20first%20supported%20Saddam%20Hussein%20during%20the%20Iran-Iraq%20War%2C%20but%20later%20overthrew%20him%20in%202003.%20In%20Syria%2C%20Western%20powers%20have%20backed%20various%20rebel%20groups%2C%20some%20of%20which%20later%20turned%20into%20destabilising%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOil%2C%20the%20region's%20most%20valuable%20resource%2C%20has%20been%20both%20a%20blessing%20and%20a%20curse.%20Oil%20drew%20intense%20interest%20from%20Western%20powers%2C%20who%20sought%20to%20control%20these%20resources%20to%20fuel%20their%20economies.%20The%20oil-rich%20Gulf%20states%2C%20while%20benefiting%20economically%2C%20became%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20Western%20security%20guarantees%2C%20leaving%20them%20vulnerable%20to%20foreign%20influence.%20The%201953%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20(CIA)-led%20coup%20in%20Iran%2C%20which%20overthrew%20Prime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Mossadegh%20after%20he%20nationalised%20the%20oil%20industry%2C%20is%20a%20case%20in%20point.%20Similarly%2C%20the%202003%20US-led%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%2C%20justified%20on%20dubious%20grounds%2C%20dismantled%20state%20institutions%20and%20unleashed%20a%20wave%20of%20sectarian%20violence%20that%20continues%20to%20plague%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael%20and%20Modern%20Wars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Balfour%20Declaration%20of%201917%2C%20in%20which%20Britain%20supported%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20home%20for%20the%20Jewish%20people%26quot%3B%20in%20Palestine%2C%20added%20to%20the%20tensions.%20This%20commitment%20conflicted%20with%20promises%20made%20to%20Arab%20leaders%20by%20the%20colonial%20powers%2C%20which%20had%20assured%20support%20for%20an%20independent%20Arab%20state%20in%20exchange%20for%20their%20rebellion%20against%20the%20Ottomans.%20The%20betrayal%20left%20deep%20scars%2C%20fuelling%20resentment%20that%20persists%20to%20this%20day.%20The%20establishment%20of%20Israel%20following%20the%20Holocaust%20and%20the%20UN%20partition%20plan%20displaced%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20first%20Arab-Israeli%20war%20in%201948.%20Subsequent%20wars%20(1956%2C%201967%2C%201973)%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20refugee%20crisis%20and%20the%20ongoing%20Israeli-Palestinian%20tensions%20continue%20to%20define%20the%20region's%20volatility.%20For%20many%20Arab%20nations%2C%20Israel%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20Western-backed%20injustice%20and%20territorial%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Death%20Of%20Pan-Arabism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20turmoil%20and%20crises%2C%20or%20perhaps%20because%20of%20them%2C%20Pan-Arabism%20emerged%20as%20a%20movement%20to%20unite%20the%20warring%20Arab%20world%20under%20a%20shared%20identity%2C%20overcoming%20tribal%20and%20sectarian%20divisions.%20Egypt's%20Gamal%20Abdel%20Nasser%20was%20the%20movement's%20most%20towering%20figure.%20Unfortunately%20for%20ordinary%20Arab%20people%2C%20internal%20rivalries%2C%20ideological%20differences%20and%20external%20meddling%20stymied%20the%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20wary%20of%20the%20socialist%20underpinnings%20of%20Pan-Arabism%2C%20actively%20worked%20to%20undermine%20it.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20CIA%20was%20reportedly%20involved%20in%20orchestrating%20coups%20and%20supporting%20conservative%20monarchies%20to%20counter%20Nasser's%20influence.%20By%20the%201970s%2C%20Pan-Arabism%20had%20largely%20faded%2C%20replaced%20by%20fragmented%20nationalisms%20and%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHope%2C%20Then%20Disillusionment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202011%20Arab%20Spring%20uprisings%20briefly%20raised%20hopes%20for%20democratic%20change.%20However%2C%20the%20movements'%20outcomes%20varied%20widely%2C%20with%20some%20states%20descending%20into%20chaos.%20In%20Syria%2C%20peaceful%20protests%20against%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20devolved%20into%20a%20brutal%20civil%20war%2C%20drawing%20in%20regional%20and%20international%20players.%20The%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Turkey%20and%20others%20have%20all%20backed%20different%20factions%2C%20turning%20Syria%20into%20a%20proxy%20battlefield.%20Libya%2C%20too%2C%20saw%20its%20long-time%20leader%20Gaddafi%20overthrown%20with%20NATO's%20help%2C%20only%20to%20descend%20into%20a%20protracted%20conflict%20among%20rival%20factions.%20Meanwhile%2C%20countries%20like%20Egypt%20saw%20a%20return%20to%20authoritarianism%2C%20dashing%20hopes%20for%20meaningful%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEchoes%20Of%20The%20Crusades%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Crusades%2C%20launched%20between%20the%2011th%20and%2013th%20centuries%2C%20were%20actually%20military%20campaigns%20by%20European%20Christian%20powers%20to%20reclaim%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20Holy%20Land%20from%20Muslim%20control.%20Salah%20ad-Din%20Yusuf%20ibn%20Ayyub%2C%20commonly%20known%20in%20the%20West%20as%20Saladin%2C%20defeated%20the%20Christian%20army%20of%20crusaders%20at%20the%20Battle%20of%20Hattin%20in%201187%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20recapture%20of%20Jerusalem.%20Ironically%2C%20Saladin%20hailed%20from%20a%20Kurdish%20family%20(non-Arabs%20in%20West%20Asia)%20but%20became%20a%20hero%20of%20the%20Arabs%20after%20the%20victory.%20The%20first%20sultan%20of%20both%20Egypt%20and%20Syria%20is%20today%20hero-worshipped%20in%20Muslim%20societies%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Arab%20world%2C%20for%20inflicting%20a%20crushing%20defeat%20on%20the%20European%20forces.%20He%20remains%20a%20celebrated%20figure%20of%20resistance%2C%20unity%2C%20and%20Islamic%20valour.%20His%20victory%20symbolises%20an%20ability%20to%20push%20back%20against%20Western%20incursions%E2%80%94a%20legacy%20still%20invoked%20today%20in%20discussions%20of%20imperialism%2C%20foreign%20intervention%20and%20the%20need%20for%20regional%20unity.%20Today%2C%20Islamist%20movements%20and%20Arab%20nationalists%20have%2C%20at%20times%2C%20likened%20Western%20intervention%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%E2%80%94such%20as%20the%20US-led%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20or%20European%20colonial%20rule%E2%80%94to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20crusade%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20continuation%20of%20Western%20aggression%20under%20different%20banners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWest%20Asia%20is%20in%20chaos.%20Visiting%20Libya%2C%20Yemen%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20Syria%20and%20Iraq%20is%20considered%20unsafe.%20It%20remains%20a%20patchwork%20of%20conflict%20zones%2C%20authoritarian%20regimes%20and%20fragile%20states.%20Over%20six%20million%20Syrians%20are%20refugees%20living%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%2C%20and%20over%20seven%20million%20are%20internally%20displaced.%20Yemen's%20civil%20war%2C%20orchestrated%20by%20Saudi-Iran%20rivalry%2C%20has%20created%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20worst%20humanitarian%20crises.%20On%20top%20of%20the%20crises%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%2C%20their%20people%20have%20to%20grapple%20with%20the%20threat%20of%20ISIS.%20Lebanon's%20economy%20is%20in%20free%20fall%2C%20exacerbating%20social%20and%20political%20tensions.%20Even%20Israel's%20economy%20has%20ground%20to%20a%20halt%20due%20to%20relentless%20wars%20in%20the%20last%2014%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20its%20Western%20allies%20remain%20deeply%20involved%20in%20the%20region%2C%20whether%20through%20military%20presence%2C%20arms%20sales%2C%20supporting%20one%20extremist%20organisation%20or%20another%2C%20or%20through%20diplomatic%20manoeuvres.%20Unfortunately%20apart%20from%20Turkey%2C%20no%20other%20emerging%20power%20or%20BRICS%20nations%20are%20showing%20any%20interest%20in%20shaping%20the%20region's%20future%2C%20even%20though%20they%20know%20they%20might%20be%20eventually%20affected%20by%20the%20ongoing%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734613140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fskbvblb_syria_160x120_09_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsyria-why-is-the-middle-east-always-in-turmoil-7286489%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Why%20is%20the%20Arab%20world%20p