d%20to%20proactive%20even%20though%20its%20actions%20affect%20the%20economy%20with%20long%20lags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20would%20have%20thought%20that%20between%20the%20commentary%20and%20forecast%20changes%20that%20the%20world%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20since%20the%20jumbo%20rate%20cut%20just%20three%20months%20ago.%20It%20clearly%20does%20not%20take%20much%20to%20cause%20this%20Fed%20to%20swing%20its%20view%20around.%20I%20can%20guarantee%20that%20it%20will%20shift%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a33c997-5215-4b0f-8fb2-c79c59a2529f%5C%22%3EStephen%20Koopman%2C%20senior%20macro%20strategist%20at%20Rabobank%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'We%20had%20a%20year-end%20inflation%20forecast%2C%20and%20it's%20kind%20of%20fallen%20apart.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20exactly%20the%20confidence-inspiring%20line%20you'd%20expect%20from%20a%20Fed%20chair.%20But%20Jerome%20Powell's%20performance%20at%20yesterday's%20press%20conference%20wasn't%20his%20finest%20hour.%20In%20what%20might%20have%20been%20the%20most%20uncomfortable%20showing%20of%20his%20tenure%2C%20Powell%20ceded%20the%20stage%20to%20the%20hawks%2C%20visibly%20strained%20as%20he%20tried%20to%20sell%20a%20strategy%20he%20didn't%20fully%20appear%20to%20endorse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20flagged%20inflation%20'moving%20sideways'%20and%20'higher%20uncertainty'%20around%20its%20trajectory.%20These%20admissions%20reveal%20a%20central%20bank%20increasingly%20unsure%20of%20its%20footing%2C%20with%20rates%20markets%20now%20expecting%20just%20one%20cut%20for%202025%20(as%20we%20do)%2C%20and%20with%20no%20real%20consensus%20on%20when%20that%20final%20cut%20would%20arrive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed25905c-ab6d-440f-b33d-9194f47902e0%5C%22%3EJamie%20Cox%2C%20managing%20partner%20for%20Harris%20Financial%20Group%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarkets%20have%20a%20really%20bad%20of%20habit%20of%20overreacting%20to%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20The%20Fed%20didn't%20do%20or%20say%20anything%20that%